Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} on to boil for the
pasta. Heat a #frying pan{} on high heat. Add the @lamb mince{200%g}(no oil!) and
cook until browned, breaking it up with a #wooden spoon{}, ~{5%minutes}. Drain
off any fat, then stir in the @tinned chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1/2%can}. Stir
in the @chicken stock powder{1/2%tsp} and @water{60%ml}. Bring to the boil, then
simmer until thickened and reduced by half, ~{15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @rigatoni pasta{160%g} in the pan of boiling water. Cook until
'al dente', around ~{12%minutes}. TIP: 'Al dente' simply means the pasta is cooked
through but has a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle. When cooked, drain in a
#colander{} and return to the pan off the heat. Drizzle with some @olive oil{1%tbsp}
to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta and lamb cook, mix the @balsamic vinegar{6%tbsp}, @honey{7.5%tbsp}
and @olive oil{1%tbsp} together in a #small bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Pop half the @hard Italian style cheese{20%g}(grated) in another #bowl{}
and add in the @panko breadcrumbs{15%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and
mix well, then set aside.

Preheat your #grill{} to medium-high. When the lamb mixture has thickened, add the
@baby spinach{62.5%g} and stir through until wilted, about ~{2%minutes}. Season
to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Mix the @creme fraiche{99%g} and remaining @hard Italian style cheese{20%g}(grated)
into the pasta. Spoon the lamb mixture into an #ovenproof dish{} and top with the
creamy pasta. Sprinkle the cheesy crumbs on top and grill for ~{2-3%minutes}. You
want the breadcrumbs to go golden brown but not burn, so watch them closely!

If everyone wants their @baby leaf mix{50%g} dressed, toss it in the dressing and
scatter over the @walnuts{20%g}. If not, just serve some rocket plain and some with
dressing. Spoon the creamy lamb pasta bake into bowls with the rocket on the side.
Enjoy!